<p>The pattern is not linear. The first 3 months feel like grinding. By month 6, hosts start referring you to other hosts. By month 9, AI search engines treat your name as a recognized entity in your topic area. By month 12, the inbound pitches outnumber the outbound ones.</p>
<p>The compounding only works if the vetting, optimization, and repurposing steps are followed every time. Skipping any one of them breaks the loop.</p>
<p>For context on how authority signals compound, read our deep dive on <a href="/blog/perplexity-seo/">the link between brand mentions and AI citations</a>.</p>
